# This whole directory is the build context, so what is excluded here is a security
# control, not a size optimisation. This repo has a habit of dropping .env files around
# (see .gitignore), and one of them landing in an image layer would ship the Event Hubs
# key to the registry — where it would sit, readable, in every pull.
#
# That is true no matter WHERE the build runs, and it is worth being precise about why:
# the LAYER is what leaks, not the upload. Even a build whose context never leaves this
# machine would bake a stray .env into an image that then gets pushed to the registry.
#
# The image needs exactly two files from this directory: red_point_detector.py and
# entrypoint.sh. Everything else is noise at best.
.env
.env.*
*.env
*.pem
*.key
*secret*
*credential*
id_rsa*
.git/

__pycache__/
*.pyc
